WEBVTT

00:04.333 --> 00:06.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.266 --> 00:07.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.600 --> 00:09.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:09.366 --> 00:10.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(GUNFIRE)

00:10.766 --> 00:12.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: The first shot, I
didn't realize was a gunshot.

00:12.600 --> 00:14.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I just heard a loud pop.

00:14.766 --> 00:18.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What
we're learning about a
gunman who opened fire
on members of Congress

00:18.933 --> 00:23.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
during an early morning baseball
practice, shooting the third
highest ranking Republican

00:25.700 --> 00:28.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the House of
Representatives, Steve
Scalise, and several others.

00:28.133 --> 00:33.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then: A massive fire at a
London apartment tower leaves at
least a dozen dead, as rescuers

00:35.233 --> 00:39.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
search for people trapped
inside the 24-story tower.

00:39.400 --> 00:43.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And is there such a
thing as clean coal?

00:43.133 --> 00:48.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
A look at the nation's
largest carbon-capturing
plant, part of a plan to
clean up the environment

00:49.333 --> 00:51.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
while keeping the
coal industry alive.

00:51.400 --> 00:53.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID GREESON, Vice President
of Development, NRG: We're just
now reaching the point where

00:53.733 --> 00:58.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this technology is mature enough
to be considered for rollout
to the broad coal-fired fleet

01:00.866 --> 01:02.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in the United States
and around the world.

01:02.933 --> 01:04.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:04.966 --> 01:05.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:05.966 --> 01:10.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A

01:19.200 --> 01:23.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
leading Republican in
the U.S. House lies
critically wounded tonight.

01:23.333 --> 01:28.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Illinois man who shot him,
along with a police officer,
a congressional staffer,

01:29.200 --> 01:31.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and a lobbyist, has died.

01:31.366 --> 01:35.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They came together in a
fusillade of bullets and
bloodshed early today,
just outside Washington.

01:37.000 --> 01:39.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Our Lisa Desjardins
begins our coverage.

01:39.500 --> 01:41.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(GUNFIRE)

01:41.566 --> 01:45.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: For at least
five minutes, gunshots crackled
across the Northern Virginia

01:47.433 --> 01:49.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
baseball field where
Republican members of
Congress were practicing.

01:49.533 --> 01:54.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Cell phone video shared with the
"NewsHour" captured a harrowing
scene of a gunfight between

01:55.433 --> 01:56.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the attacker and Capitol Police.

01:56.233 --> 01:57.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Hey.

01:57.233 --> 01:59.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Is that guy OK out there?

01:59.700 --> 02:02.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Has that guy been shot?

02:02.100 --> 02:03.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is he OK?

02:03.100 --> 02:05.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Is anybody talking to him?

02:05.166 --> 02:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The man who
shot the video, Noah Nathan,
had been out walking his dogs.

02:07.200 --> 02:09.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NOAH NATHAN, Eyewitness: I saw
the congressional players, and,
you know, they're a regular

02:09.633 --> 02:11.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
here practicing in the morning.

02:11.900 --> 02:14.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And then I heard -- I
thought it was fireworks.

02:14.366 --> 02:17.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then I heard another
one and realized, OK,
maybe that's not fireworks.

02:17.166 --> 02:19.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
It's gunfire.

02:19.233 --> 02:20.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And then people started
scattering, and then
there was more shots
and you could hear them

02:20.766 --> 02:23.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
skimming off the gravel
and hitting the fence.

02:23.700 --> 02:24.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it was a helpless feeling.

02:24.700 --> 02:26.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I couldn't do anything.

02:26.733 --> 02:30.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: As lawmakers
jumped over fences, seeking
cover, House Majority Whip

02:30.133 --> 02:33.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Steve Scalise was
shot in the hip.

02:33.000 --> 02:34.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Alabama Congressman
Mo Brooks saw it all.

02:34.733 --> 02:36.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:36.866 --> 02:38.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MO BROOKS (R), Alabama: It's
the feeling of helplessness,
when you have got a baseball

02:38.966 --> 02:42.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
bat and a guy's got a rifle.

02:42.066 --> 02:47.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you see your friends,
Steve Scalise in particular,
lying on the ground, dragging

02:49.033 --> 02:51.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
himself from the infield dirt
to the outfield grass, and
there was nothing we could do to

02:51.366 --> 02:53.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
help him.

02:53.333 --> 02:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Georgia
Congressman Barry Loudermilk
says it wasn't a random attack.

02:55.633 --> 02:57.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:57.166 --> 02:59.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARRY LOUDERMILK (R), Georgia:
There were civilians out there.

02:59.166 --> 03:00.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There were people walking their
dogs, laying on the ground
screaming and crying, but he

03:00.100 --> 03:01.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
wasn't targeting them.

03:01.033 --> 03:03.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He was shooting at us.

03:03.066 --> 03:05.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Joe Barton
of Texas had taken his
young sons to the practice.

03:05.233 --> 03:07.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:07.366 --> 03:08.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOE BARTON (R), Texas: We got
some of us were in the dugout,
some of us were on the ground.

03:08.166 --> 03:10.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I was behind the dugout.

03:10.600 --> 03:14.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
My son Jack got under an SUV.

03:14.533 --> 03:17.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And he was very brave.

03:17.333 --> 03:20.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
My other son Brad was
in the batting cage and
he also was very brave.

03:20.533 --> 03:23.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: In the video,
you can hear people shouting
for police to shoot the gunman.

03:23.800 --> 03:25.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Shoot him!

03:25.033 --> 03:26.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS:
Again, Mo Brooks:

03:26.100 --> 03:28.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:28.166 --> 03:31.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MO BROOKS: The bravery that
they displayed, taking on a
guy with the rifle while they

03:31.266 --> 03:36.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have pistols, shooting from
long distance, and if they
had not been successful, then

03:38.266 --> 03:40.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the tragedy here would have
undoubtedly been much greater,
because those of us who were

03:40.733 --> 03:43.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in the first base dugout,
we'd of had no chance.

03:43.166 --> 03:46.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS:
First-responders were on
the scene in minutes.

03:46.033 --> 03:49.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some victims were airlifted
to hospitals by helicopter.

03:49.166 --> 03:52.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Scalise underwent surgery and
was in critical condition.

03:52.000 --> 03:56.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The suspected shooter was
also taken to the hospital,
where he died of his wounds.

03:56.900 --> 04:01.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Police identified him as
66-year-old James Hodgkinson
of Belleville, Illinois.

04:01.366 --> 04:06.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TIMOTHY SLATER, FBI: Law
enforcement has reason to
believe that the shooter
has been in Alexandria,

04:07.566 --> 04:12.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Virginia, area since
March of this year.

04:12.166 --> 04:17.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The FBI has issued again
a seeking information
poster that is located
on our Web site asking

04:18.733 --> 04:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the public to come forward with
information on the shooter.

04:23.133 --> 04:28.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Florida
Congressman Ron DeSantis
believes he talked with
Hodgkinson just before

04:28.733 --> 04:29.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the shooting.

04:29.266 --> 04:31.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:31.333 --> 04:33.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RON DESANTIS (R), Florida: An
unidentified individual walked
up to the car, asked Congressman

04:33.400 --> 04:37.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Duncan, who was in the front
passenger seat, whether they
were Republicans or Democrats

04:37.400 --> 04:38.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the field.

04:38.400 --> 04:40.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It was a little bit abrasive.

04:40.466 --> 04:42.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was something that kind of
struck me as odd, not odd to
the extent I thought he was

04:42.566 --> 04:44.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
going to go shoot people.

04:44.566 --> 04:48.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Already,
a picture has begun to
emerge of Hodgkinson.

04:48.566 --> 04:53.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A Facebook page of the same
name is filled with anti-Trump
posts, and Hodgkinson apparently

04:53.433 --> 04:56.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
volunteered for Bernie
Sanders' presidential campaign.

04:56.166 --> 04:59.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Vermont senator today
condemned the shooting
on the Senate floor.

04:59.833 --> 05:01.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

05:01.533 --> 05:04.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
BERNIE SANDERS (I),
Vermont: I am sickened
by this despicable act.

05:04.900 --> 05:09.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And let me be as
clear as I can be.

05:11.300 --> 05:15.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Violence of any kind is
unacceptable in our society.

05:15.500 --> 05:19.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I condemn this action in
the strongest possible terms.

05:19.566 --> 05:24.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: There is a
contrast between the location
of this shooting, a neighborhood

05:24.533 --> 05:28.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that is known for putting up
signs of welcome and opposing
hate, and this act of violence

05:28.500 --> 05:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that some say may symbolize
rising anger in America.

05:32.433 --> 05:36.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the scene, Virginia Governor
Terry McAuliffe specifically
pointed to politics.

05:36.500 --> 05:38.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GOV.

05:38.533 --> 05:40.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TERRY MCAULIFFE (D), Virginia:
What you saw in the last
presidential campaign, there's

05:40.566 --> 05:44.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
just a lot of dug-in hard
feelings out there that
exist in this country today.

05:46.566 --> 05:50.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I do think our country
has become way too divided
between red and blue.

05:50.633 --> 05:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: President
Trump echoed the cry for unity
at the White House hours after

05:54.200 --> 05:56.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the shooting.

05:56.300 --> 05:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States: We may have our
differences, but we do well

05:59.133 --> 06:04.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in times like these to remember
that everyone who serves in
our nation's capital is here

06:06.666 --> 06:10.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
because, above all,
they love our country.

06:10.900 --> 06:15.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The House
canceled votes for the day,
but shaken lawmakers, Democrats

06:15.600 --> 06:19.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and Republicans alike,
gathered on the House floor
in a show of solidarity.

06:19.100 --> 06:20.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

06:20.600 --> 06:23.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker
of the House: We are united.

06:23.433 --> 06:27.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We are united in our shock,
we are united in our anguish.

06:27.433 --> 06:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
An attack on one of us is
an attack on all of us.

06:33.066 --> 06:34.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(APPLAUSE)

06:34.066 --> 06:36.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

06:36.600 --> 06:39.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA),
House Minority Leader:
We cannot let that be a
victory for the assailant

06:39.700 --> 06:41.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
or anyone who would
think that way.

06:41.400 --> 06:43.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, tomorrow, we will
go out on the field.

06:43.700 --> 06:45.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We will root for our team.

06:45.300 --> 06:48.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We want everyone to do
his or her very best.

06:48.700 --> 06:53.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we will use this occasion
as one that brings us together
and not separates us further.

06:55.400 --> 06:58.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: An
update on conditions.

06:58.133 --> 07:02.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Congressman Scalise and one
other staffer who was shot
are in critical condition.

07:02.266 --> 07:05.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The others injured
today, we're told, are in
good or fair condition.

07:05.833 --> 07:10.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, also, about that baseball
game, it is scheduled to be,
as planned, tomorrow night.

07:11.566 --> 07:13.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They are not canceling.

07:13.600 --> 07:17.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And Judy, they're adding
another charity cause,
the Fallen Officers Fund.

07:17.100 --> 07:22.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Lisa, are
there changes in security as
a result of what happened?

07:23.600 --> 07:25.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: I
think the answer to
that, Judy, is not yet.

07:25.133 --> 07:27.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Here, of course, the Capitol
is a highly secure building.

07:27.700 --> 07:28.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There's no changes here.

07:28.933 --> 07:31.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
No one said there
need to be changes.

07:31.466 --> 07:34.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there is a real
question about these
events where many members
of Congress gather in one

07:34.133 --> 07:36.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
place.

07:36.133 --> 07:39.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Congressman Scalise's security
detail was there today, as
well as one other Capitol

07:39.533 --> 07:42.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
police officer because so
many congressmen were present.

07:42.900 --> 07:47.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're wondering if there
need to be more of a police
presence when there are not just

07:49.500 --> 07:51.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
leaders, but any members
of Congress gathered
in one place like that.

07:51.400 --> 07:56.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, Lisa,
you're at that Capitol Building
every day, practically.

07:56.033 --> 07:57.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How are people
dealing with this?

07:57.833 --> 08:01.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: I think the
mood today, Judy, is sober.

08:01.133 --> 08:06.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's not highly emotional, but
it's one where they are taking
very serious stock of where

08:06.100 --> 08:10.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we are as a nation and where
people are in terms of how
they look at their leaders and

08:10.600 --> 08:12.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
how they look at violence.

08:12.666 --> 08:16.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think there's also a lot of
questions today about whether
political rhetoric has, indeed,

08:18.966 --> 08:22.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
gone too far, and whether the
divides that affect the votes
on the House and Senate floor

08:24.833 --> 08:28.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are reverberating back and
forth with public divides now
rising into anger and violence.

08:30.066 --> 08:32.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lisa
Desjardins, who covers the
Capitol every day for us.

08:32.566 --> 08:36.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lisa, you have been on this
story all day from the moment
you heard about it this morning.

08:36.800 --> 08:37.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you very much.

08:37.833 --> 08:39.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: My pleasure.

08:39.900 --> 08:43.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we are now
joined by the managers of the
two congressional baseball

08:43.866 --> 08:46.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
teams that were practicing this
morning in different places.

08:46.833 --> 08:51.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They are Republican
Representative Joe Barton
of Texas, who, as you
just saw, was at this

08:51.766 --> 08:56.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
morning's Republican baseball
practice, and Democratic
Representative Michael Doyle of

08:57.366 --> 08:58.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Pennsylvania.

08:58.600 --> 09:01.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Gentlemen, welcome
to the program.

09:01.233 --> 09:02.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Congressman Barton,
to you first.

09:02.700 --> 09:04.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
First of all, we're so glad
that you are all right.

09:04.766 --> 09:06.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We saw that you were
there with your two sons.

09:06.833 --> 09:07.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How are you doing?

09:07.833 --> 09:08.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

09:08.833 --> 09:11.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JOE BARTON: We're doing fine.

09:11.833 --> 09:14.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Everybody was looking
out for my two sons.

09:14.533 --> 09:19.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And thank gosh -- God that the
Capitol Police were there and
immediately returning fire,

09:21.533 --> 09:25.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
which diverted the gunman
from attacking the members
who were on the field.

09:25.300 --> 09:29.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Did you
feel there was anything
more that could have
been done this morning?

09:29.633 --> 09:30.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

09:30.633 --> 09:31.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOE BARTON: Not really.

09:31.933 --> 09:34.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I mean, we practice
in a public park.

09:34.733 --> 09:35.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There's a dog park.

09:35.966 --> 09:37.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's a YMCA by
the baseball field.

09:37.966 --> 09:40.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
There are joggers.

09:40.000 --> 09:44.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are -- it's just, you
know, most mornings, there are
people out doing their exercise

09:46.100 --> 09:48.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and walking their dogs.

09:48.866 --> 09:53.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We don't make any attempt
to restrict people from
watching the practice.

09:55.900 --> 09:59.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This individual who did the
shooting, some of the members
think they saw him yesterday,

10:01.366 --> 10:06.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and, while I thought he had
just driven in, apparently, he
had been in the area for some

10:06.733 --> 10:09.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
time.

10:09.300 --> 10:12.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I don't -- I don't
know how you can function
in an open democracy,
especially in the House

10:14.666 --> 10:19.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of Representatives,
with 435 members, and
not have public access.

10:21.100 --> 10:25.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, again, this game has been
played for about over 100 years.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's never been
anything like this before.

10:28.966 --> 10:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Congressman
Doyle, where were you
when you heard this?

10:34.000 --> 10:34.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And what did you think?

10:34.900 --> 10:36.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

10:36.766 --> 10:38.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE DOYLE (D), Pennsylvania:
So, we were in the
middle of our practice.

10:38.833 --> 10:42.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We were having batting practice,
and I was standing behind home
plate, you know, instructing

10:43.933 --> 10:45.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our batters.

10:45.566 --> 10:49.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And I got a text message
from one of my staff
saying, are you OK?

10:51.166 --> 10:53.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I was puzzled by
the -- by the text.

10:53.233 --> 10:58.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then I saw right below it
a news clip saying, shooter
at congressional baseball

11:00.366 --> 11:03.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
practice, and realized at that
moment that it had to be over
at the Republican practice.

11:06.000 --> 11:10.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I called my team off the
field, because we didn't have
much information at the time,

11:12.733 --> 11:16.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to get them over in the dugout,
and let them all know what
happened and what I was hearing.

11:18.466 --> 11:22.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there was sort of a --
I call it a stunned silence
with most of the players.

11:23.933 --> 11:27.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We just couldn't
believe something like
this was happening.

11:27.033 --> 11:29.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And there wasn't much we
could do where we were.

11:29.900 --> 11:34.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we basically just huddled up
and started saying some prayers
for our Republican colleagues

11:36.366 --> 11:38.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that they'd be safe and that
nobody would be hurt badly.

11:38.900 --> 11:43.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, after that, you know, the
reports started to flood into
our phones and we just, you

11:45.066 --> 11:47.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
know, were reading them
like everyone else.

11:47.066 --> 11:51.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Congressman
Barton, and, again, we know that
you both were practicing for

11:53.133 --> 11:55.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
this congressional game, annual
congressional game that's
taking place tomorrow night.

11:55.766 --> 11:57.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You're going ahead with it.

11:57.933 --> 12:02.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is the -- I just asked Lisa
Desjardins this question, our
reporter at the Capitol, and

12:04.866 --> 12:08.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
she said this is -- the reaction
there has been sober, that
people are -- to some extent,

12:09.966 --> 12:12.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
members may be rethinking
whether things have
gotten too partisan.

12:12.066 --> 12:13.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What do you think?

12:13.066 --> 12:15.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

12:15.133 --> 12:19.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOE BARTON: Well, the reaction
here has been very supportive
of the Republicans on the

12:19.533 --> 12:21.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
team.

12:21.500 --> 12:25.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Congressman Doyle and his
Democratic players have
reached out to us personally.

12:27.433 --> 12:30.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The speaker and Mrs.
Pelosi, the minority leader,
have talked directly.

12:32.866 --> 12:36.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Everybody is supportive because,
we are -- we have an R or an
D by our name, but our title

12:44.200 --> 12:49.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
- - our title is United
States representative.

12:50.666 --> 12:55.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I'm very proud to be
a member of the Congress.

12:56.966 --> 13:00.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I'm proud to serve with
people like Mike Doyle.

13:00.333 --> 13:05.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, you know, we feel very
blessed that we're here
to have this interview.

13:07.333 --> 13:11.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Had the shooter not been
attacked by the Capitol
Hill Police, who risked
their lives -- and

13:13.966 --> 13:18.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
two of them got shot -- had he
gotten inside the fence of the
field and gotten to the first

13:20.700 --> 13:25.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
base dugout, there were 20,
15 members, and five or six
staffers in that dugout huddled

13:29.033 --> 13:30.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
down.

13:30.733 --> 13:33.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's actually a lowered,
below-the-field dugout.

13:33.400 --> 13:36.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And there would have been
no place for them to run.

13:36.533 --> 13:38.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, it could have
been much worse.

13:38.933 --> 13:43.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Congressman
Doyle, I can see the pain
in both of your faces.

13:45.833 --> 13:48.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is this a time for coming
together in some way and for
rethinking, as we said, some of

13:52.733 --> 13:53.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the partisanship?

13:53.733 --> 13:55.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:55.300 --> 13:59.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MIKE DOYLE: I think all of us
are reflecting on that today.

13:59.233 --> 14:03.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Joe and I have been associated
with this game for quite a
while, and we have been friends

14:03.566 --> 14:05.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for a long time.

14:05.766 --> 14:10.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His son Jack is like one of
my nephews, always comes up
and asks me how I'm doing.

14:12.700 --> 14:16.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I always tries to get
intelligence from Jack on what
his dad is up to, and Jack never

14:17.566 --> 14:18.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
gives him up.

14:18.500 --> 14:19.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So he's a good kid that way.

14:19.833 --> 14:20.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

14:20.833 --> 14:22.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

14:22.933 --> 14:26.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE DOYLE: But I got to tell
you, there was a real feeling
of helplessness on our part

14:26.433 --> 14:30.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as we stood there in the
dugout reading the reports
that were coming in.

14:30.900 --> 14:33.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We know -- we know
all these guys.

14:33.666 --> 14:35.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They're our friends.

14:35.833 --> 14:40.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We may have differences
politically, but they're
our friends, and we care
about them very much.

14:42.566 --> 14:47.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think all of us are
reflecting on how each one of us
individually can set an example

14:49.466 --> 14:54.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the country, too, because
when people see their leaders
being uncivil towards one

14:54.133 --> 14:59.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
another, then you start to
see the public being uncivil
towards one another and towards

14:59.066 --> 15:00.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their leaders.

15:00.433 --> 15:02.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I think that's
got to change.

15:02.433 --> 15:06.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So maybe it starts with
us, and maybe this will
change some attitudes here.

15:08.966 --> 15:11.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Congressman
Barton, I hear and I see the
affection between the two of

15:11.300 --> 15:16.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
you, and I am seeing and hearing
you say it exists with others.

15:16.233 --> 15:21.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I think it's fair to
say, it doesn't always come
across in the news coverage.

15:21.000 --> 15:22.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

15:22.533 --> 15:25.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOE BARTON: Well, politics in
Washington is a contact sport.

15:25.033 --> 15:28.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it shouldn't be a
personal animosity sport.

15:28.466 --> 15:32.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And with Mike and I and a lot
of other members, it's not.

15:32.866 --> 15:35.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I do want to apologize for
getting emotional a minute ago.

15:35.233 --> 15:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, Tom Hanks was the
manager of a women's baseball
team, and, in that movie, he has

15:42.233 --> 15:44.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the famous line, there's
no crying in baseball.

15:44.833 --> 15:49.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, there's certainly no
-- shouldn't be any crying
in congressional baseball.

15:49.200 --> 15:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I do apologize for my
emotional outburst a minute ago.

15:55.066 --> 15:55.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: No -- no...

15:55.766 --> 15:56.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

15:56.766 --> 15:58.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

15:58.833 --> 16:00.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE DOYLE: I would say
there's lots of members of
Congress that get along.

16:00.766 --> 16:03.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We tend to not be
the ones the media is
interested in interviewing.

16:03.333 --> 16:07.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Oftentimes, the media's
interested in interviewing
the two that are throwing
the swords at each

16:07.833 --> 16:09.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
other.

16:09.866 --> 16:13.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, maybe the news media,
too, can reflect a little bit
on that and show some of the

16:15.000 --> 16:16.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
positive things that
take place down here.

16:16.533 --> 16:17.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:17.533 --> 16:18.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JOE BARTON: That's true.

16:18.966 --> 16:20.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And that's
something for us to reflect on.

16:20.466 --> 16:22.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Well, we so appreciate the two
of you being together right now.

16:22.433 --> 16:25.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And no apology needed,
Congressman Barton.

16:25.233 --> 16:30.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's entirely understandable
why you would be emotional
at a time like this.

16:30.833 --> 16:32.066 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We thank you.

16:32.066 --> 16:33.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We're thankful that
you are all right.

16:33.600 --> 16:36.066 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
We thank you for
talking with us.

16:36.066 --> 16:37.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Congressman Doyle, thank you.

16:37.133 --> 16:38.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We thank you both.

16:38.400 --> 16:39.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

16:39.400 --> 16:41.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MIKE DOYLE: Thank you.

16:41.100 --> 16:44.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And now to
the day's other major story.

16:44.466 --> 16:49.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is in London, where a
fast-moving fire engulfed a
high-rise apartment building.

16:50.866 --> 16:53.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It killed at least 12
people and injured scores.

16:53.133 --> 16:57.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have a report from Dan
Rivers of Independent Television
News, and with a warning: Some

16:57.600 --> 17:00.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the images and sounds
may be disturbing.

17:00.100 --> 17:05.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAN RIVERS: With horrifying
ferocity, the fire consumed
Grenfell Tower in minutes, a

17:11.200 --> 17:16.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
24-floor inferno from which
there was no escape for some.

17:16.166 --> 17:21.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trapped by smoke and flames,
residents signaled their plight
from on high as the building

17:22.100 --> 17:27.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
disintegrated around them.

17:30.666 --> 17:35.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On this mobile phone footage,
the cries for help are chilling.

17:36.633 --> 17:39.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
MAN: Help!

17:39.700 --> 17:41.800 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Help!

17:41.800 --> 17:46.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: We saw people looking out
of the windows, screaming help,
screaming, help, help, flashing

17:48.300 --> 17:49.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
their lights and everything.

17:49.733 --> 17:53.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And now all those windows,
people are gone, literally gone.

17:53.566 --> 17:56.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MAN: I saw one person
trying to jump out.

17:56.133 --> 17:59.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One actually jumped out,
and obviously what happened.

17:59.600 --> 18:01.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's just a nightmare.

18:01.733 --> 18:06.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAN RIVERS: The streets around
Grenfell Tower were soon full
of those who escaped its flames,

18:08.533 --> 18:13.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
children among those suffering
from the acrid fumes.

18:15.533 --> 18:19.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An exhausted little girl
is cradled as the shock
and bewilderment sink in.

18:24.400 --> 18:26.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Many here have lost everything.

18:26.633 --> 18:31.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some are still unsure what's
happened to neighbors,
friends, loved ones.

18:31.366 --> 18:35.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And, above them,
the fire raged on.

18:35.233 --> 18:40.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
As the sky lightened,
the flames continued
to devour the building.

18:43.166 --> 18:48.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This was the view from the
SOUTH BANK, the plume of
smoke visible for 20 miles.

18:49.700 --> 18:52.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
With daylight, stories
of extraordinary escape
started to emerge.

18:52.366 --> 18:54.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SAMIRA LAMRANI, Witness: A
lady appeared at the window,
gesturing, body language, from

18:54.866 --> 18:57.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
what she was saying, I'm
about to throw my baby,
please catch the baby.

18:57.333 --> 19:02.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And the baby, I think,
was wrapped in some sort
of bed sheet, blanket.

19:03.200 --> 19:07.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And she threw the baby.

19:07.333 --> 19:09.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As the baby came down -- and
this was about approximately
from the ninth or 10th floor

19:09.400 --> 19:13.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
- - a member of the public,
a gentleman ran forward and
miraculously grabbed the baby.

19:15.566 --> 19:18.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, like I said, above you,
from the left, from the right,
mostly kids, it was harrowing,

19:21.466 --> 19:24.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
torturing screams
for help, young kids.

19:24.133 --> 19:29.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I think also, where
the fire was now spread,
people were reaching out
