storage capacity underneath the
continental United States to

45:03.766 --> 45:06.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
last about 900 years
of CO2 production.

45:06.600 --> 45:10.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it's just a question of
societal priorities and whether
we want to pay a little more for

45:10.500 --> 45:13.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
power to get the
carbon dioxide out.

45:13.033 --> 45:15.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Miles
O'Brien, thanks very much.

45:15.400 --> 45:16.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN:
You're welcome, Judy.

45:16.933 --> 45:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now: a new
national voice for poetry.

45:30.300 --> 45:35.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In a tradition dating back to
1937, the Library of Congress
selects a prominent writer to

45:37.233 --> 45:41.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
serve as the country's poet
laureate for terms that have
ranged from one to three years.

45:43.566 --> 45:46.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The goal, according to
the library, to raise the
national consciousness
to a greater appreciation

45:48.033 --> 45:50.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the reading and
writing of poetry.

45:50.200 --> 45:54.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The new laureate was revealed
today, and our Jeffrey Brown
had a chance to talk with her

45:54.700 --> 45:56.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
earlier this week.

45:56.666 --> 46:01.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Empathy and
self-awareness through language,
that is the creed that comes

46:03.566 --> 46:08.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
through in talking with 45 year
old Tracy K. Smith, writer,
teacher, spouse and mother

46:10.366 --> 46:14.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of three, including 4-year-old
twins, and now taking on a very
public role as the nation's

46:15.533 --> 46:17.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
poet laureate.

46:17.500 --> 46:19.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRACY K. SMITH,MD-B U.S.
Poet Laureate: This is a
position that allows me to kind

46:19.533 --> 46:23.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of profess publicly all that
I really hold true privately,
that, if we can listen actively

46:28.133 --> 46:33.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
enough, if we can put
enough pressure on
ourselves and our thought
process, language can be a

46:33.866 --> 46:36.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
real tool of revelation.

46:36.166 --> 46:41.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I love being able to do
that with my students
and my little seminars.

46:43.100 --> 46:47.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I love the idea that maybe
there's a way that this position
allows me to do that with

46:47.066 --> 46:49.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
my fellow Americans.

46:49.200 --> 46:53.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Smith is
author of three books
of poetry, including the
Pulitzer Prize-winning

46:55.566 --> 46:59.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"Life on Mars," in part an elegy
for her father, who served in
the Air Force before leaving

47:00.000 --> 47:02.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to work on the Hubble telescope.

47:02.700 --> 47:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In her 2015 memoir titled
"Ordinary Light," she
writes of growing up in
a tight-knit middle-class

47:09.933 --> 47:14.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
family in Northern California,
a coming-of-age tale exploring
love and loss, race and faith,

47:17.600 --> 47:20.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a theme that
suffuses her poetry.

47:20.033 --> 47:25.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRACY K. SMITH: I wasn't even
aware that that's what I was
doing until after my last book

47:25.033 --> 47:28.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
of poems came out, and
I realized, wow, there's
a -- these poems are
thinking about space,

47:28.666 --> 47:32.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but they're also searching
for God, in a way.

47:32.333 --> 47:35.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think it comes back to
that sense that I grew up with
that there is something large

47:35.833 --> 47:38.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that we can cleave
to, if we choose to.

47:38.833 --> 47:43.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I wanted to figure out if
there was a way that the artist
in me and the 21st century

47:50.433 --> 47:55.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
academic in me could
find something like a
plausible version of God
or a plausible version

47:58.400 --> 48:03.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the afterlife that I would
be willing to claim publicly.

48:04.733 --> 48:06.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think that language
facilitated that.

48:06.833 --> 48:10.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Another
big area that you're
often exploring is race.

48:10.533 --> 48:15.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, in your memoir,
you talk explicitly
about sort of comparing
your upbringing to your

48:17.466 --> 48:21.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
parents and your grandparents,
the differences there, but
also things that have remained.

48:23.700 --> 48:26.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TRACY K. SMITH: A lot
of my awareness of how
race had imprinted by
my parents, who grew

48:28.833 --> 48:32.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
up in the segregated South,
a lot of that was shaped by a
sense of sadness and a sense

48:34.900 --> 48:39.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of anxiety on my part that made
me not want to talk about it.

48:39.366 --> 48:44.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, there were a lot of silences
that I was drawn to explore
in writing about that time

48:46.200 --> 48:50.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that I had never felt capable
of bringing into speech
when I was growing up.

48:52.766 --> 48:56.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As I get older, I realize the
history that felt so ancient
when I was growing up is so

48:56.600 --> 49:01.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
- - so close to us and present
in ways that I had never
imagined, or didn't want to let

49:04.033 --> 49:06.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
myself imagine
when I was a child.

49:06.333 --> 49:11.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, writing about it, I think,
is a way of reckoning with
what is yet to be resolved

49:13.200 --> 49:16.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about the present moment, about
how we are willing to love
each other, even though we

49:20.333 --> 49:22.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
look different from one another.

49:22.633 --> 49:27.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Smith has
been a professor at Princeton
since 2005 and now heads its

49:29.700 --> 49:32.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
creative writing program,
teaching small seminars to
young poets in the making.

49:34.333 --> 49:37.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Here especially, she
says, the emphasis is
on how we use language.

49:37.566 --> 49:42.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRACY K. SMITH: Yes, this
is our library and one of
our favorite classrooms.

49:42.466 --> 49:47.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want them to start thinking
that a poem isn't just an
expression of all these things

49:47.033 --> 49:52.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that you're feeling, but
it's a set of choices that
you're making in language.

49:53.966 --> 49:57.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, every description, every
question, every statement, every
turn is a choice that opens

49:59.633 --> 50:01.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
up or closes off
certain possibilities.

50:01.866 --> 50:05.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you don't always think
about that when you're sitting
down to write in the flush

50:05.533 --> 50:06.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of emotion.

50:06.533 --> 50:07.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But thinking about...

50:07.966 --> 50:09.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: I mean, the
feelings are part of it, right?

50:09.166 --> 50:10.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TRACY K. SMITH: The
feelings are part of it.

50:10.633 --> 50:11.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And the
expression is part of it.

50:11.866 --> 50:14.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But you're saying the
language choices...

50:14.333 --> 50:17.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TRACY K. SMITH: Beyond
that, yes, the language
can help you get some
traction in those feelings.

50:17.233 --> 50:19.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
"One of the women greeted me.

50:19.533 --> 50:22.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
'I love you,' she said.

50:22.233 --> 50:27.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She didn't know me, but I
believed her, and a terrible new
ache rolled over in my chest."

50:29.233 --> 50:33.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: To hear some of
her language, Smith read part
of a new poem titled "Wade

50:34.566 --> 50:36.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the Water."

50:36.700 --> 50:40.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRACY K. SMITH: "I love you
throughout the performance in
every hand clap, every stomp.

50:42.533 --> 50:47.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I love you in the rusted iron
chains someone was made to drag
until love let them be unclasped

50:50.233 --> 50:52.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and left empty in the
center of the ring."

50:52.566 --> 50:57.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Now Tracy K.
Smith will have a prominent
voice, a very public national

50:58.733 --> 51:01.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
platform, to reach
new audiences.

51:01.500 --> 51:06.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
If you think about the
tumultuous times we're
in technologically, all
kinds of changes around

51:06.233 --> 51:11.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
us, if you think about
the divisions politically
at this moment, it seems
like an appropriate

51:13.333 --> 51:15.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
moment to say, why poetry?

51:15.500 --> 51:16.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Why bother?

51:16.600 --> 51:18.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Why bother being a poet?

51:18.100 --> 51:20.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What kind of impact could you
possibly have, amidst all that?

51:20.966 --> 51:23.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
TRACY K. SMITH: Mm-hmm.

51:23.033 --> 51:27.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I will say that a poem
allows or requires you to
submit to something else.

51:30.133 --> 51:31.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Often...

51:31.133 --> 51:33.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Submit means?

51:33.200 --> 51:35.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TRACY K. SMITH: That's one of
the things we don't want to
do, to say, OK, I'm not the

51:35.233 --> 51:36.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
expert.

51:36.233 --> 51:37.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
You're the expert.

51:37.233 --> 51:39.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Let me listen.

51:39.600 --> 51:43.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Let me respond to
something that's completely
counterintuitive for
me, that pulls me toward

51:45.200 --> 51:48.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a different sense
of what's valuable.

51:48.533 --> 51:53.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think, when we do that with
a work of art, we're learning
how to do that in real time

51:55.500 --> 51:57.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with other people.

51:57.033 --> 51:59.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Does that mean
even making us better citizens?

51:59.533 --> 52:01.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TRACY K. SMITH: I think so.

52:01.766 --> 52:03.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Poems remind us of that.

52:03.366 --> 52:07.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Poems remind us that someone
is saying, come here.

52:07.766 --> 52:09.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This has happened to me.

52:09.100 --> 52:10.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is how it made me feel.

52:10.700 --> 52:13.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is who I am in
the wake of this thing.

52:13.933 --> 52:17.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And we all have
stories like that.

52:17.033 --> 52:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they're important to honor,
and they're important also
to say, maybe my story helps

52:24.600 --> 52:29.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
me listen and cherish this
other person's story, too.

